parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sending unit can cause the fuel gauge to report inaccurate fuel levels, leading to engine stalling, sputtering, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge reports inaccurate fuel levels
engine stalling
sputtering
fuel gauge fluctuating between full and empty
fuel range indicator decreasing rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the fuel pump housing can cause fuel leaks, potentially leading to fires, especially in the K-series motorcycles where the leak is over the cylinder heads.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
potential fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel system can cause the engine to shut off unexpectedly, leading to potential accidents, especially when combined with inaccurate fuel level readings.
symptoms: Engine shutting off unexpectedly
fuel gauge malfunctioning
fuel range indicator decreasing rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling at Low Speed Deceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling at low speed deceleration can cause the motorcycle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially in heavy traffic or when navigating turns, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies when slowing down to a stop
typically when the clutch is pulled in and the throttle is rolled off
often at speeds below 2000 RPM. The stalling may occur intermittently
with some owners experiencing it once every 30-50 stops.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling at low speeds can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when it happens in curves or on the freeway.
symptoms: The engine shuts off when coming to a stop at low speeds
the bike needs to be in a complete stop and switched to neutral to restart
the issue occurs randomly
and it can happen multiple times in a single ride.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge indicator to become inoperable, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in unexpected stalling, stranding the driver, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge indicator is not functioning
the fuel level reading is inaccurate
the vehicle stalls due to empty fuel tank
the fuel level sensor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A crack in the fuel pump flange can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a fire, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel leak
crack observed in fuel pump flange
fuel pump flange failure.
